Up to July 1985,{Courtmoor School}had a timetable lasting from 8.45am to 3.40pm, similar to most other schools.
In September, 1985, Courtmoor is introducing a{"continental" type day.}
Pupils will register at 8.30am. Following assembly, the first two lessons will be divided by a 5 minutes "changeover" time and pupils will not have a proper break until 11.10. This will last 20 mins and snacks will be on sale. A similar break will follow the third lesson at 12.50 and the school day will end at 2.20pm, when meals will be available. It is hoped that the earlier finish to the day will allow more activities to take place after school, whilst allowing pupils and teachers more time with their own families.
